      "role": "user",
      "content": "sometimes i just sit here staring at the ceiling and thinking about how everything is just... nothing. like, if you look at the scale of the universe, everything we do, every single thing we feel or care about, it’s just a tiny blip that gets erased eventually. it feels like such a joke to even try to build a life or care about anything when the end result of the universe is just cold, empty silence anyway. what's even the point of the struggle?",
